comments.text:
When I was a kid my mother would take us to the local diner on Fridays for dinner, and they had those table side juke boxes.  She would give my sister and I quarters to play songs.  

This song must have just come out as I was obsessed with this tune, and I would play it so many times in a row.  I remember saying to my mother that I’d love to meet Ringo Starr not realizing at the time who he was or who he used to play with. 

I was about 9 or 10 when this song came out, and I remember asking for a kazoo for my birthday that year.  

I want to say to you that your content is awesome my man, and I am really enjoying the videos you’re putting out.
comments.author: @SaratogaYouthMentor
